message.body: Hello - how's it going?
Hey, going fine. Just joined the study, you?
Things are great - the weather is perfect in boston. Where do you live?
I'm in Philly. How do you like Boston? I've heard mixed reviews
It's alright - definitely grew on me over time - the people are abrasive and it's crazy expensive to live, but there are jobs and things to do but i lovephilly a lot more though
Yeah, I've mainly heard that its very expensive and a bit isolated. Gotta love that east coast abrasive-ness!
Definitely - it's also super segregated. I found philly to be much more mish-mash ed with people and cultures. What do you do not philly?
What do I not do? Hah, i'm a composer/performer. And right now, I'm catering full-time for money.
That's awesome! Music composition?
Yeah. What about you?
That's great - what kind of music do you compose? I work at a healthcare Improvement non profit - kind of like a think tank for innovative healthcare ideas
Wow, that's great
Something this country desperately needs, that's for sure
Are you in Boston permanently?
Not sure - my wife and I loved here so she could go to law school - she just graduated and we're both employed here - we'll probably think about shippingout in 3 to 5 years
How long have you been in philly
About 8 years, moved here from the west coast
Nice, I grew up in Las Vegas before moving to philly for college
Cool. Yeah, my partner and I trying to decide whether we should move
Or look into buying a home
Back to the west coast?
in philly
The buyer's market here is nuts right now - it's bubbling for some reason
What part of philly?
Not sure
I'm living in fairmount now
